<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-05-16T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-05-16T21:00:00-05:00" n="425" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d425">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/3192: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-17T10:00:00+08:00">May 17, 1938—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received noon.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>675. Following from Hankow.</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“May 16, noon. Reference telegram May 13, 7 a.m. from Foochow
                                regarding protection of Americans there. Please expedite reply,
                                repeat Foochow’s telegram to Tokyo and add following: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>‘Unless you see reasons to the contrary, I suggest that it
                                        would he advisable to notify Japanese Government of
                                        concentration of American nationals at Tsangchienshan at
                                        Foochow, and in addition supply list of places in the
                                        interior at which Americans now are.’</p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <p>You will doubtless wish to make similar communication to the Japanese
                                authorities at Shanghai. Please repeat to Washington. Johnson.”</p>
                        </quote>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>